com.horse.pokemon.ObjectData.PokemonData

Class EffortValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.horse.pokemon.ObjectData.PokemonData.EffortValue

  • public class EffortValue
extends java.lang.Object
    Class for storing the value for a Pokemon that will raise each stat according to its corresponding EffortValue stat. There is a mutable and immutable EffortValue for each stat. The immutable stat is for when a Pokemon is defeated and the winner gains EffortValue points. The mutable value is the changing number for when the opposing Pokemon is defeated (They keep track of the EV's).
    See Also:
    Pokemon, IndividualValue
